replies.body:
I started writing this, and then I got bored and tried to stretch my vocabulary as far as I could. I'm in Vietnam atm with relatives, so I don't get much of a chance to be as extensively recherche' in my use of the english language. Also sometimes it's fun to try to be as verbose as possible, sure the message could be expressed far more frankly, but I feel alot of people ignore the whimsicality that can be found in language and writing.

I feel the movement encouraging the simplification of everyday language and literature rather artless. I admit there is great impact in being concise, and simple language is far less prone to errors, but sometimes flowerly description, musical pacing and structure, or simply selecting the most appropriate word, should be more relevant in writing for leisure.

I was not trying to express 'pseudo-intellect', I guess I was just unconsciously venting because I miss english.{{item:3070}}
